[[Air Marshal]] '''Sir Gilbert Edward Nicholetts''' [[Knight Commander of the Order of the British Empire|KBE]] [[Companion of the Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Air Force Cross (United Kingdom)|AFC]] [[Medal bar|& Bar]] (9 November 1902 &ndash; 7 September 1983) was a senior commander in the [[Royal Air Force]] during the 1950s.

==RAF career==
Nicholetts joined the Royal Air Force in 1921.<ref name=air>[http://www.rafweb.org/Biographies/Nicholetts.htm Air of Authority - A History of RAF Organisation - Air Marshal Sir Gilbert Nicholetts]</ref> He was appointed Officer Commanding [[No. 228 Squadron RAF|No. 228 Squadron]] just at the start of [[World War II]].<ref name=air/> He went on to be Station Commander at [[RAF Haifa]] and then [[RAF Shallufa]] before being taken [[Prisoner of War]] in 1942.<ref name=air/> After the War he became Senior Air Service Officer at Headquarters [[No. 25 Group RAF|No. 25 (Armament) Group]] and then Air Officer Commanding the Central Photographic Establishment before becoming Director of Organisation at the [[Air Ministry]] in 1948.<ref name=air/> He was then made Senior Air Service Officer at Headquarters [[RAF Coastal Command]] in 1951, Air Officer Commanding [[No. 21 Group RAF|No. 21 Group]] in 1953 and Air Officer Commanding [[AHQ Malta]] in 1956.<ref name=air/> His last appointment was as [[Inspector-General of the RAF]]<ref>[http://www.flightglobal.com/pdfarchive/view/1958/1958%20-%200807.html Royal Visit to Air Trainers] Flight International, 20 June 1958</ref> in 1958 before retiring in 1959.<ref name=air/>

